JSON EditorThe following is the JSON syntax for the dateFacet type.
Replace the default index definition with the following. To learn more
about the fields, see the following table.```json
{
  "mappings": { 
    "dynamic": true | false, 
    "fields": { 
        "<fieldName>": {
            "type": "objectId"
        }
    } 
  }
}
```The MongoDB Search `objectId` type takes the following option:| UI Field Name | JSON Option | Type   | Necessity | Description                                                                   |
| ------------- | ----------- | ------ | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Data Type     | type        | string | required  | Human-readable label that identifies this field type. Value must be objectId. |The following index definition examples use collections in the
[sample data sets](available-sample-datasets). After you
[Load Sample Data Into Atlas](load-sample-data), you can use
these examples to index fields as the dateFacet type.To learn how to set up and run the following example code, see
Define the Index for the token Type.Create an index on a field with the objectId type.```javascript
{
  "mappings": { 
    "dynamic": false, 
    "fields": { 
        "title": {
            "type": "objectId"
        }
    } 
  }
}

```You can use the MongoDB Search `objectId` type to index [ObjectId](manual/reference/bson-types) values. You can query fields of type
`objectId` using the [equals](equals-ref) and [in](in-ref)
operators.You can also use the `objectId` type to index:* Fields whose value is an array of `objectId`. To learn more, see
  [How to Index the Elements of an Array](fts-array-ref).

* `objectId` fields inside an array of documents indexed as the
  [embeddedDocuments](bson-data-types-embedded-documents) type.If you enable [dynamic mappings](static-dynamic-mappings), MongoDB Search
automatically indexes fields of type dateFacet. You can
use the **Visual Editor** or the  **JSON Editor** in the Atlas UI to
index fields as the dateFacet type.
